description: Resources are tested during a training exercise as germ warfare threatens the capital.
synopsis_small: Resources are tested during a training exercise as germ warfare threatens the capital.
synopsis_medium: The team take part in an EERIE (Extreme Emergency Response Initiative Exercise). They must act exactly as if there's a national emergency.
synopsis_large: The team is busy at work when an alarm goes off. Everyone groans - it's an EERIE (Extreme Emergency Response Initiative Exercise). They must act exactly as if there's a national emergency - in this case, germ warfare in Central London.As the exercise goes ahead, information dries up, power and phone lines go down, victims try to break into Thames House - and suddenly Harry gets sick. The team tries to stay calm, but doubts start to set in. Is this actually for real?
